<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-03T12:21:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-03T12:21:00-05:00" n="844" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5561: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Helsingfors</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Haynes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Helsingfors</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-03T19:00:00+01:39"><hi rend="italic">November 3,
                                        1919—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:27
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>489. Officially reported <persName corresp="#p_YGNN1">Yudenitch</persName> has retreated from Gatchina and Luga and both
                            places taken by Bolsheviki.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Haynes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>